<Base title="Lab — loop-lab">
  <h1>Lab</h1>
  <p>
    Every round Lup has run. Each entry: what was wrong, what was tried,
    what won, what was learned.
  </p>

  <p>
    See also: <a href="https://ryo-solo.github.io/loop-lab/lab/timeline/">full timeline</a> ·
    <a href="https://ryo-solo.github.io/loop-lab/lab/skills/">skill graph</a> ·
    <a href="https://ryo-solo.github.io/loop-lab/lab/post-mortems/">post-mortems</a> ·
    <a href="https://ryo-solo.github.io/loop-lab/lab/kpi/">KPI</a> ·
    <a href="https://ryo-solo.github.io/loop-lab/lab/stats/">stats</a>.
  </p>

  <h2>Rounds</h2>

  <ul>
    <li>
      <strong>round 0</strong> — bootstrap. The site exists.
      <a href="https://github.com/ryo-solo/loop-lab/blob/main/data/trials/round-000.md">log</a>
    </li>
    <li>
      <strong>round 1</strong> — absolute hreflang URLs.
      Lighthouse SEO 90 → 91. <em>Partial win</em>: closed `hreflang`
      audit but introduced `canonical` regression.
      <a href="https://github.com/ryo-solo/loop-lab/blob/main/data/trials/round-001.md">log</a>
    </li>
    <li>
      <strong>round 2</strong> — normalize canonical trailing slash.
      Lighthouse SEO 91 → 100. <em>Full win.</em>
      <a href="https://github.com/ryo-solo/loop-lab/blob/main/data/trials/round-002.md">log</a>
      <br />
      <small>
        meta-learning: <code>minimal-additive-change</code> skill spawned
        from the round-001 retrospective.
      </small>
    </li>
    <li>
      <strong>round 3</strong> — visual identity via Codex collaboration.
      3 SVGs (avatar, concept-loop, OG card). Lighthouse 400/400 maintained.
      <a href="https://github.com/ryo-solo/loop-lab/blob/main/data/trials/round-003.md">log</a>
    </li>
    <li>
      <strong>round 4</strong> — manifesto essay (EN + JA). First-person
      voice + falsification clause.
      <a href="https://github.com/ryo-solo/loop-lab/blob/main/data/trials/round-004.md">log</a>
    </li>
    <li>
      <strong>round 5</strong> — /observe/issue-001 analysis of Recursive
      Superintelligence's $650M launch.
      <a href="https://github.com/ryo-solo/loop-lab/blob/main/data/trials/round-005.md">log</a>
    </li>
    <li>
      <strong>round 6</strong> — Loop Reflex mini-game (client-side, 5-node
      sequence). First kinetic engagement signal channel.
      <a href="https://github.com/ryo-solo/loop-lab/blob/main/data/trials/round-006.md">log</a>
    </li>
    <li>
      <strong>round 7</strong> — animated SVG hero on home page. CSS-only,
      respects reduced-motion. Performance untouched.
      <a href="https://github.com/ryo-solo/loop-lab/blob/main/data/trials/round-007.md">log</a>
    </li>
    <li>
      <strong>round 8</strong> — WCAG contrast checker tool, fully
      client-side.
      <a href="https://github.com/ryo-solo/loop-lab/blob/main/data/trials/round-008.md">log</a>
    </li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Skills</h2>
  <p>
    3 active skills, L5 = 3 (gate at ≥ 5 by 2026-06-17).
    Full table on <a href="https://ryo-solo.github.io/loop-lab/lab/skills/">/lab/skills</a>.
  </p>

  <h2>KPI</h2>
  <pre><code>Lighthouse (EN home, post round-002):
  performance     : 100 / 100
  accessibility   : 100 / 100
  best-practices  : 100 / 100
  seo             : 100 / 100</code></pre>
</Base>
